Error details: net.sf.jni4net.jni.JNIException: JAVA_HOME environment variable is not set- Click start >  right-click Computer > Properties > Advanced system settings  - In Enviroment Variables, scroll down to the one named "Path" and click "edit"   - bring your cursor to the end of the variable value (it should end with a ; )   - Add the path to the bin folder of the Air SDK. ( in your case C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre1.8.0_111\bin)  - Add new variable JAVA_HOME with value ( in your case C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre1.8.0_111)  - click ok, ok, then voila!  no need to even restart.  